Hey, guys, came on!

248
00:19:09,464 --> 00:19:10,499
SAM:
Let's go!

249
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:13,545
PETER: Sam, just get back on the bus.
We can talk about it.

250
00:19:13,702 --> 00:19:15,682
Molly, Sam, came on, guys.

251
00:19:20,309 --> 00:19:22,186
Did he seem weird to you
when he get on the bus?

252
00:19:22,344 --> 00:19:24,085
No, he was fine. it's like he just snapped.

253
00:19:24,246 --> 00:19:26,920
-What's going on?
-What the hell is going on out here?

254
00:19:32,187 --> 00:19:35,191
[CABLES SNAPPING]

255
00:19:36,058 --> 00:19:37,162
DENNIS:
We should, uh ....

256
00:19:37,326 --> 00:19:38,532
ISAAC:
Holy shit!

257
00:19:38,694 --> 00:19:40,173
DENNIS:
Get off the bus!

258
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:44,840
[CROWD SCREAMING]

259
00:19:55,244 --> 00:19:56,279
SAM:
Come on!

260
00:20:17,866 --> 00:20:19,174
How did you know?

261
00:20:28,043 --> 00:20:29,716
MAN:
That's the big question here.

262
00:20:30,612 --> 00:20:32,182
How did you know?

263
00:20:33,382 --> 00:20:35,089
It says right here in your statement:

264
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:38,823
"l saw it collapse.
I knew it would happen."

265
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:40,557
That sounds premeditated to me.

266
00:20:40,722 --> 00:20:42,633
No, no, no. That's not what I meant.

267
00:20:44,993 --> 00:20:47,269
I had a vision.

268
00:20:47,696 --> 00:20:50,233
Okay. A vision.

269
00:20:50,399 --> 00:20:53,437
Psychic phenomena, ghosts, Bigfoot.

270
00:20:53,602 --> 00:20:55,582
You actually believe in that stuff?

271
00:20:55,737 --> 00:20:56,772
I don't know.

272
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:01,252
I'll tell you what I believe:

273
00:21:01,410 --> 00:21:03,287
There's an answer for everything.

274
00:21:03,445 --> 00:21:05,948
There's an answer for why
you knew to warn everyone...

275
00:21:06,114 --> 00:21:09,584
...the bridge was going to collapse,
and minutes later, it did.

276
00:21:09,751 --> 00:21:14,063
I told you, I saw it coming.
I don't know how.

277
00:21:14,222 --> 00:21:15,530
I just did.

278
00:21:17,359 --> 00:21:19,305
And no one else did?

279
00:21:19,461 --> 00:21:23,102
Like I said, it just came out of nowhere.

280
00:21:23,265 --> 00:21:24,869
Did Sam have issues with authority?

281
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:28,776
Did he ever demonstrate
any sort of extremist behavior?

282
00:21:28,937 --> 00:21:30,143
No.

283
00:21:31,606 --> 00:21:34,382
Wait. "Extremist behavior"?

284
00:21:34,843 --> 00:21:36,618
You mean like a terrorist?

285
00:21:36,778 --> 00:21:40,316
You see him talk to anyone that morning?
On a cell phone, pay phone?

286
00:21:40,482 --> 00:21:41,825
Just his girlfriend.

287
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:45,456
His ex-girlfriend, I mean. Molly.

288
00:21:45,620 --> 00:21:48,464
-But that was in person.
-Molly.

289
00:21:49,658 --> 00:21:50,728
Ex.

290
00:21:50,892 --> 00:21:52,462
BLOCK:
Tell me about the breakup.

291
00:21:52,627 --> 00:21:56,666
Was he upset? Scale of 1 to 10.

292
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:58,810
It's personal.

293
00:22:00,068 --> 00:22:03,709
You must have been pissed, right?
Getting dumped like that.

294
00:22:03,872 --> 00:22:05,852
What does that have to do
with anything?

295
00:22:06,208 --> 00:22:08,916
I'm just trying to get all the pieces
of the puzzle together...

296
00:22:09,077 --> 00:22:12,251
...before I start moving them around,
making them fit.

297
00:22:12,681 --> 00:22:17,824
Lack, I just had a hunch that something
had was gonna happen. That's it.

298
00:22:17,986 --> 00:22:19,329
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

299
00:22:20,288 --> 00:22:21,858
Excuse me.

300
00:22:25,027 --> 00:22:27,064
Forensics came back with the analysis.

301
00:22:27,829 --> 00:22:29,934
-And?
-They're chalking it up to high winds...

302
00:22:30,098 --> 00:22:32,044
...and structural damage
from the construction.

303
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:33,543
"High winds"?

304
00:22:33,702 --> 00:22:35,682
AGENT:
Yeah. Send everyone home.

305
00:22:37,372 --> 00:22:38,407
You're free to go.

306
00:22:44,946 --> 00:22:48,223
I have a feeling
we'll be seeing each other again.

307
00:22:48,383 --> 00:22:49,726
Call it a hunch.

308
00:22:57,192 --> 00:23:00,298
WOMAN [ON TV]: Authorities are calling
the North Bay Bridge collapse...

309
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:02,237
...a freak act of nature...

310
00:23:02,397 --> 00:23:07,073
...citing a highway improvement project
that may have weakened the superstructure.

311
00:23:07,235 --> 00:23:11,206
Among the survivors were eight employees
of Presage Paper...

312
00:23:11,373 --> 00:23:13,410
...on their way to a business retreat.

313
00:23:13,575 --> 00:23:16,920
The other 17 employees
were killed in the collapse.

314
00:23:17,079 --> 00:23:19,958
And although they've been branded
the "lucky eight"...

315
00:23:20,115 --> 00:23:24,222
...the surviving employees
new face an uncertain future.

316
00:23:44,072 --> 00:23:45,312
NATHAN:
Hey, guys.

317
00:23:45,474 --> 00:23:46,578
MOLLY:
Hey.

318
00:23:46,741 --> 00:23:47,811
PETER:
Hey.

319
00:23:49,311 --> 00:23:52,656
Anybody know
when this thing's supposed to start?

320
00:23:52,814 --> 00:23:56,159
When Dennis gets here, I guess.

321
00:23:57,919 --> 00:23:59,592
That agent still hounding you?

322
00:24:00,155 --> 00:24:04,262
No. You heard the news,
it was natural causes.

323
00:24:04,993 --> 00:24:06,597
Yeah, more like supernatural.

324
00:24:08,163 --> 00:24:10,871
How you holding up? I tried calling.

325
00:24:11,032 --> 00:24:14,377
No, yeah, I saw. I was just tired.

326
00:24:16,404 --> 00:24:17,644
ISAAC:
So?

327
00:24:19,274 --> 00:24:20,981
How did you explain it?

328
00:24:23,845 --> 00:24:25,153
I didn't.

329
00:24:26,348 --> 00:24:27,383
I couldn't.

330
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:29,324
Sam, there had to be a reason.

331
00:24:29,484 --> 00:24:31,896
Heh. That is exactly
what the agent kept saying.

332
00:24:36,124 --> 00:24:39,537
Whatever answer you're lacking for,
I don't have it.

333
00:24:39,694 --> 00:24:42,038
Yeah, Sam's right.
It doesn't matter how it happened.

334
00:24:42,197 --> 00:24:45,576
We should all just put it behind us
and be grateful we're still alive.

335
00:24:48,470 --> 00:24:50,848
Definitely beats the alternative, right?

336
00:24:51,072 --> 00:24:52,915
DENNIS:
I look out at the faces today...

337
00:24:53,074 --> 00:24:56,681
...and I see family members, friends.

338
00:24:57,546 --> 00:25:02,086
But the people that left us on the bridge
that day, they were more than that.

339
00:25:02,717 --> 00:25:04,754
People like Jennifer Alcott...

340
00:25:06,955 --> 00:25:08,366
...Chris Boylan...

341
00:25:10,091 --> 00:25:11,229
...David Buckler.

342
00:25:12,494 --> 00:25:14,496
Maybe you worked next to them.

343
00:25:14,663 --> 00:25:16,404
Maybe you worked for them.

344
00:25:16,565 --> 00:25:20,342
But we all worked with them, huh?

345
00:25:20,535 --> 00:25:23,607
Who can forget Trevor Wino's smile?

346
00:25:26,241 --> 00:25:27,777
Or Isaac Palmer.

347
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:29,987
Did he just say my name?

348
00:25:30,145 --> 00:25:31,453
[OLIVIA SNORTS]

349
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:33,593
-That's not funny.
-I know, I'm sorry.

350
00:25:33,748 --> 00:25:36,661
I just get weird with tragedies. I'm sorry.

351
00:25:38,687 --> 00:25:39,893
[WHISPERS]
I see dead people.

352
00:25:40,055 --> 00:25:41,466
[OLIVIA LAUGHING]

353
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:42,897
Guys.

354
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,606
Death...

355
00:25:56,004 --> 00:25:57,574
...doesn't like to be cheated.

356
00:25:58,240 --> 00:25:59,514
Excuse me?

357
00:25:59,774 --> 00:26:01,117
What's that supposed to mean?

358
00:26:05,780 --> 00:26:08,954
You all just be careful now.

359
00:26:09,117 --> 00:26:11,256
PETER:
Okay. Thanks for the advice!

360
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,458
Creepy guy.

361
00:26:13,622 --> 00:26:16,626
[BLUDWORTH WHISTLING
"LEANING ON THE EVERLASTING ARMS"]

362
00:26:36,311 --> 00:26:39,417
COOK:
How's that foie gras, Sam? Waiting on you.

363
00:26:48,757 --> 00:26:50,168
[TERRY POISON'S "BALLROOM"
PLAYING]

364
00:26:50,325 --> 00:26:53,795
Wasted like a drunk
She drank, drunk, drunk

365
00:26:53,962 --> 00:26:55,703
Stop it

366
00:26:55,864 --> 00:26:57,309
It's not forgotten

367
00:26:58,166 --> 00:26:59,201
COOK 1:
Thanks.

368
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:00,573
COOK 2:
Got my dessert?

369
00:27:05,974 --> 00:27:07,248
[MIKE CLEARS THROAT]

370
00:27:08,710 --> 00:27:10,018
What's the matter with it?

371
00:27:10,178 --> 00:27:12,385
Said it was flat. No flavor.

372
00:27:13,615 --> 00:27:15,561
-Do they want something else?
MIKE: Yeah.

373
00:27:15,717 --> 00:27:16,889
The check.

374
00:27:19,788 --> 00:27:21,768
Let me taste it.

375
00:27:27,162 --> 00:27:30,632
The customer is an asshole.
The bourguignon is good.

376
00:27:42,911 --> 00:27:44,549
MOLLY:
Hold on.

377
00:27:57,425 --> 00:27:58,768
You mind if I came in?

378
00:27:58,927 --> 00:28:00,838
Yeah. Sure.

379
00:28:11,005 --> 00:28:12,040
Thanks.

380
00:28:12,207 --> 00:28:14,016
I thought you'd be working tonight.

381
00:28:14,175 --> 00:28:17,418
Yeah. You know,
I worked the first shift, but...

382
00:28:18,513 --> 00:28:20,686
...there was something else I needed to do.

383
00:28:22,784 --> 00:28:25,458
[WHISTLING]

384
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:28,028
-Can l...?
-Oh.

385
00:28:28,189 --> 00:28:30,829
Yeah. Sure, go ahead.

386
00:29:14,869 --> 00:29:17,440
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

387
00:29:24,646 --> 00:29:25,750
Thank you.

388
00:29:27,348 --> 00:29:28,520
Listen ....

389
00:29:30,218 --> 00:29:32,721
When everything started going down
on that bridge...

390
00:29:35,990 --> 00:29:38,664
...the only thing I thought about
was you.

391
00:29:39,861 --> 00:29:41,807
Getting you to safety.

392
00:29:42,430 --> 00:29:46,003
You are the only thing
I care about, Molly.

393
00:29:48,803 --> 00:29:51,374
Whatever's wrong, I can fix it.

394
00:29:51,539 --> 00:29:53,951
You haven't done anything wrong.

395
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:56,989
Then, what? What is it?

396
00:29:58,513 --> 00:29:59,548
Paris.

397
00:29:59,848 --> 00:30:01,327
We talked about that.

398
00:30:01,483 --> 00:30:06,364
I'm not going to uproot my life,
leave you, for that jab.

399
00:30:06,521 --> 00:30:09,024
But it's the only thing
you've ever dreamed of.

400
00:30:11,793 --> 00:30:13,739
Life is too short, Sam.

401
00:30:13,895 --> 00:30:16,466
You have to go after what you love.

402
00:30:17,465 --> 00:30:18,705
I am.

403
00:30:23,304 --> 00:30:25,215
You should take the jab.

404
00:30:27,141 --> 00:30:29,417
Go to Paris.

405
00:30:45,894 --> 00:30:47,430
-Hey.
CANDICE: Hey.

406
00:30:47,595 --> 00:30:49,006
What's the matter?

407
00:30:49,531 --> 00:30:52,705
I don't know. I'm not ready.
I don't feel ready.

408
00:30:52,867 --> 00:30:56,337
It's been really hard to concentrate
after everything.

409
00:30:57,372 --> 00:30:58,680
Yeah? Are you sure?

410
00:30:59,374 --> 00:31:00,682
Yeah.

411
00:31:00,842 --> 00:31:03,755
Because this is the last practice
before the championship.

412
00:31:04,212 --> 00:31:06,419
And it's your last practice
of your college career.

413
00:31:06,581 --> 00:31:08,322
CANDICE:
I know, but ....

414
00:31:09,918 --> 00:31:12,159
I think you get this.

415
00:31:13,454 --> 00:31:15,195
-Really?
PETER: Yeah.

416
00:31:16,057 --> 00:31:18,162
I mean, you love it out there.

417
00:31:19,727 --> 00:31:21,229
Okay. You're right.

418
00:31:21,396 --> 00:31:23,637
And besides, coach would kill me. Heh.

419
00:31:23,798 --> 00:31:25,368
Yeah.

420
00:31:25,533 --> 00:31:26,637
Here.

421
00:31:28,703 --> 00:31:30,239
Thanks.

422
00:31:30,405 --> 00:31:31,577
Come here.

423
00:31:34,142 --> 00:31:35,348
Bye.

424
00:31:37,111 --> 00:31:38,886
PETER:
You get this.

425
00:31:48,623 --> 00:31:51,502
MAN 1: You have to get a little more speed.
You gotta hit that follow-up.

426
00:31:55,863 --> 00:31:59,208
GIRL 1: I'm sore from the back extensions.
GIRL 2: Really?

427
00:32:05,073 --> 00:32:06,643
Okay, seriously, this is stupid.

428
00:32:06,808 --> 00:32:09,311
They've gotta make it cooler
or we're gonna pass out.

429
00:32:09,477 --> 00:32:11,013
They're working on it.

430
00:32:11,179 --> 00:32:13,250
CANDICE:
Well, they Should have it fixed by new.

431
00:32:13,414 --> 00:32:16,395
[BEEPING]

432
00:32:36,904 --> 00:32:39,282
COACH:
Come on, Candice. You're up.

433
00:32:49,183 --> 00:32:50,958
PETER:
Come on, Candice. You get this.

434
00:33:17,145 --> 00:33:20,285
COACH:
Candice, now.

435
00:33:26,788 --> 00:33:29,826
MAN 1:
Really strong value on this.

436
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:43,013
GIRL 3:
Hey, coach! How was that?

437
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:05,794
MAN 1: I wanna see you guys
run the routine all the way through once.

438
00:34:24,145 --> 00:34:25,180
-That's good.
-Whew.

439
00:34:25,346 --> 00:34:27,383
MAN 1:
All right, Janine next. Let's go.

440
00:34:27,548 --> 00:34:29,858
Let's go, ladies, and drink water.

441
00:34:34,789 --> 00:34:35,824
That's it.

442
00:34:36,290 --> 00:34:38,292
Every time, Candice.

443
00:34:43,331 --> 00:34:45,072
-There you go.
-Thanks.

444
00:34:45,233 --> 00:34:47,179
COACH:
Nicely done, Candice.

445
00:34:52,006 --> 00:34:53,542
Okay, go to bars.

446
00:34:53,708 --> 00:34:55,847
WOMAN:
Come on. Hit the floor. You can do it.

447
00:34:58,346 --> 00:35:00,257
PETER:
Go hard this time, Candice.

448
00:35:01,182 --> 00:35:02,627
Let's be aggressive.

449
00:35:03,885 --> 00:35:07,492
COACH:
Here we go, Candice. Stay loose.

450
00:35:08,389 --> 00:35:10,096
MAN 2:
Okay, Porter, it's your turn.

451
00:35:11,359 --> 00:35:12,963
Stay focused.

452
00:35:14,362 --> 00:35:15,636
MAN 3:
Good.

453
00:35:21,702 --> 00:35:23,477
COACH:
Looking good, Candice.

454
00:35:54,836 --> 00:35:56,975
[SCREAMING]

455
00:36:01,142 --> 00:36:03,622
[YELLING]

456
00:36:04,645 --> 00:36:05,680
[GIRLS SCREAMING]

457
00:36:05,847 --> 00:36:07,349
Candice? Candice?!

458
00:36:07,515 --> 00:36:09,825
GIRL 4: Oh, what happened?
MAN 1: Don't touch her.

459
00:36:09,984 --> 00:36:11,691
COACH:
Someone call 911.

460
00:36:11,853 --> 00:36:12,888
Candice?

461
00:36:15,022 --> 00:36:17,400
[AMBULANCE SIREN BEEPS]

462
00:36:20,394 --> 00:36:22,396
[CHATTERING]

463
00:36:34,308 --> 00:36:36,083
Peter.

464
00:36:50,324 --> 00:36:52,167
I came as soon as I heard.

465
00:36:55,830 --> 00:36:57,468
She was doing great.

466
00:37:00,067 --> 00:37:03,514
She was almost finished with her routine
and then ....

467
00:37:10,645 --> 00:37:12,522
Why did it happen?

468
00:37:15,249 --> 00:37:17,729
This doesn't make any sense.

469
00:37:17,885 --> 00:37:19,592
I don't know, man.

470
00:37:22,890 --> 00:37:25,393
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry, Peter.

471
00:37:39,006 --> 00:37:40,986
Let's just go, Sam.

472
00:37:55,256 --> 00:37:56,735
Hey.

473
00:37:57,191 --> 00:37:58,966
How's it going?

474
00:37:59,994 --> 00:38:01,871
It's weird.

475
00:38:02,930 --> 00:38:04,500
Being here, I mean.

476
00:38:06,634 --> 00:38:08,443
It's just so quiet.

477
00:38:09,804 --> 00:38:12,785
Yeah, well, Dennis had all the calls
rerouted to corporate.

478
00:38:13,708 --> 00:38:16,814
Yeah, well, it's depressing.

479
00:38:20,314 --> 00:38:23,295
Holy crap. Did you guys
get your bereavement pay yet?

480
00:38:27,955 --> 00:38:29,093
Hey, what's he doing here?

481
00:38:29,924 --> 00:38:32,336
I think he just needed the distraction.

482
00:38:32,526 --> 00:38:33,971
Yeah.

483
00:38:34,929 --> 00:38:36,875
Yeah, that's a bummer about Candice.

484
00:38:37,665 --> 00:38:40,111
Guess we all should have seen
that coming.

485
00:38:42,603 --> 00:38:43,775
What?

486
00:38:43,938 --> 00:38:47,818
You see the crazy shit those gymnasts do.
I'm surprised it doesn't happen more often.

487
00:38:49,210 --> 00:38:51,486
MAN [OVER SPEAKERPHONE]:
Once you've handled the e-mail...

488
00:38:51,645 --> 00:38:54,524
...you'll need to deactivate all the key cards
of the deceased employees.

489
00:38:54,682 --> 00:38:56,218
Instructions are in your binder.

490
00:38:56,384 --> 00:38:59,661
Well, shouldn't that be the jab
of the facility manager?

491
00:39:00,388 --> 00:39:02,459
The facility manager's dead.

492
00:39:03,157 --> 00:39:04,227
[SIGHS]

493
00:39:04,392 --> 00:39:06,394
Dennis, you want me to fly someone
up there?

494
00:39:06,594 --> 00:39:07,902
No, no, I get it.

495
00:39:15,603 --> 00:39:16,741
Aw, Debbie.

496
00:39:22,676 --> 00:39:24,849
You were so naughty.

497
00:39:34,188 --> 00:39:35,565
[COINS JINGLING]

498
00:39:38,726 --> 00:39:40,034
Fuck it.

499
00:39:47,334 --> 00:39:49,143
Robert, my man.

500
00:39:58,546 --> 00:39:59,854
Ow.

501
00:40:02,450 --> 00:40:03,793
Shit.

502
00:40:10,424 --> 00:40:12,665
You shouldn't have, buddy.

503
00:40:24,038 --> 00:40:25,540
Hey, man, what are you doing up here?

504
00:40:25,706 --> 00:40:29,279
Had to get off the factory floor, man.
Roy's driving me crazy.

505
00:40:29,810 --> 00:40:32,654
