01:15:52,580 --> 01:15:55,652
I could just grab somebody
and pull them into an alley.

1014
01:15:56,250 --> 01:15:59,823
Or just shave somebody off a curb
into traffic.

1015
01:16:00,588 --> 01:16:02,033
You know?

1016
01:16:02,856 --> 01:16:04,130
It'd be real easy.

1017
01:16:07,194 --> 01:16:09,435
Peter, what did you do?

1018
01:16:17,137 --> 01:16:19,583
-Did you...?
-No, I didn't.

1019
01:16:22,476 --> 01:16:24,547
I couldn't.

1020
01:16:24,712 --> 01:16:26,555
I realized that...

1021
01:16:26,714 --> 01:16:29,627
...I couldn't kill somebody
that didn't deserve to die.

1022
01:16:31,719 --> 01:16:35,428
And I thought about Candice,
and I thought, "Wait a minute.

1023
01:16:36,457 --> 01:16:39,370
Candice didn't deserve to die.

1024
01:16:41,362 --> 01:16:44,104
Olivia didn't. Dennis didn't.

1025
01:16:44,898 --> 01:16:46,468
I don't."

1026
01:16:48,369 --> 01:16:49,677
Do I?

1027
01:16:49,903 --> 01:16:52,076
No, of course you don't.

1028
01:16:55,009 --> 01:16:56,454
Well...

1029
01:16:57,611 --> 01:17:03,721
...none of us deserve to die,
then why is it...

1030
01:17:05,019 --> 01:17:08,000
...that you deserve to live, Molly?

1031
01:17:09,923 --> 01:17:11,197
You said it yourself...

1032
01:17:12,393 --> 01:17:13,565
...you don't.

1033
01:17:16,430 --> 01:17:17,602
[GUNSHOT]

1034
01:17:19,266 --> 01:17:20,677
Go!

1035
01:17:21,402 --> 01:17:25,976
Repeat, shots fired.
Requesting backup. 1026 Washington.

1036
01:17:26,707 --> 01:17:30,120
Hide and I'll distract him.
When you can, go.

1037
01:17:32,212 --> 01:17:33,691
PETER:
Not done yet, Sam.

1038
01:17:36,350 --> 01:17:37,658
Where is she?

1039
01:17:39,687 --> 01:17:43,464
-Where is she?!
-I'm not gonna let you hurt her, Peter.

1040
01:17:43,657 --> 01:17:45,466
You're gonna have to kill me first.

1041
01:17:45,659 --> 01:17:47,832
Well, that doesn't do me any good.
Heh, heh.

1042
01:17:47,995 --> 01:17:49,235
Death's after you too.

1043
01:17:49,396 --> 01:17:51,774
This is crazy, Peter. Don't do this.

1044
01:17:52,933 --> 01:17:56,540
Just think for a minute, all right?

1045
01:17:56,704 --> 01:17:58,308
You are not a killer.

1046
01:17:59,673 --> 01:18:01,311
I don't wanna kill anybody, Sam.

1047
01:18:04,678 --> 01:18:05,884
I don't wanna die yet either.

1048
01:18:06,046 --> 01:18:07,457
[BOTH GRUNT]

1049
01:18:12,753 --> 01:18:15,097
Heh. it's not your time yet.

1050
01:18:24,098 --> 01:18:26,271
Don't worry, Molly...

1051
01:18:28,435 --> 01:18:30,005
...I didn't kill him.

1052
01:18:32,439 --> 01:18:36,148
But I didn't need to, Molly...

1053
01:18:37,244 --> 01:18:41,317
...because Death
is gonna do that for me.

1054
01:18:41,782 --> 01:18:44,160
Doesn't mean I can't help it.

1055
01:18:46,120 --> 01:18:47,827
That's it.

1056
01:19:29,530 --> 01:19:32,773
-Are you okay? What's going on?
-it's Peter. He has a gun.

1057
01:19:32,933 --> 01:19:34,435
[GUNFIRE]

1058
01:19:38,005 --> 01:19:39,678
Oh, my God.

1059
01:19:43,076 --> 01:19:44,783
You killed him.

1060
01:19:52,152 --> 01:19:53,654
It's Sam's turn.

1061
01:19:59,726 --> 01:20:02,206
MOLLY:
Peter, just go.

1062
01:20:02,596 --> 01:20:05,805
You have Block's life, you're safe now.

1063
01:20:06,667 --> 01:20:08,146
Please.

1064
01:20:08,368 --> 01:20:10,245
I'm sorry, Molly.

1065
01:20:12,439 --> 01:20:15,181
But you just witnessed the murder
of a federal agent.

1066
01:20:17,845 --> 01:20:22,351
And I'm not gonna spend
the life I just earned in prison.

1067
01:20:23,483 --> 01:20:24,689
[MOLLY SCREAMS]

1068
01:20:28,121 --> 01:20:31,364
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1069
01:20:33,827 --> 01:20:36,433
Molly, go! Go get help!

1070
01:21:04,224 --> 01:21:06,602
You son of a bitch!

1071
01:21:44,631 --> 01:21:47,874
Tell Candice I love her.

1072
01:21:48,235 --> 01:21:49,270
Peter.

1073
01:22:15,228 --> 01:22:18,402
It's gone. You killed him.

1074
01:22:19,199 --> 01:22:21,008
So does that mean I get Block's life?

1075
01:22:21,835 --> 01:22:23,280
[MOLLY SCREAMS]

1076
01:22:26,006 --> 01:22:27,508
Yeah.

1077
01:22:28,208 --> 01:22:30,119
I guess I do.

1078
01:22:46,093 --> 01:22:47,595
Do you mind if I take the window seat?

1079
01:22:47,995 --> 01:22:51,033
-You're gonna make me sit in the middle?
-Uh-huh.

1080
01:22:51,198 --> 01:22:53,371
SAM: I'm like twice your size.
-Not really.

1081
01:22:53,533 --> 01:22:55,535
-All right.
MAN 1: Sit down.

1082
01:22:55,702 --> 01:22:58,046
MAN 2: I'll remove him.
GUY: Fuck you. I'll remove myself.

1083
01:22:58,205 --> 01:22:59,411
GIRL:
Get off him!

1084
01:22:59,573 --> 01:23:00,847
Settle down!

1085
01:23:01,008 --> 01:23:03,887
-Came on, Browning! Come on, you punk!
-Get off the plane!

1086
01:23:04,044 --> 01:23:06,524
Get off the plane. You don't understand!

1087
01:23:06,680 --> 01:23:08,387
LEWTON:
Everybody just stay where you are.

1088
01:23:10,684 --> 01:23:14,325
-What's all that about?
-I have no idea.

1089
01:23:14,488 --> 01:23:17,594
PILOT [OVER PA]: Ladies and gentlemen,
we'll be pulling away from the gate as--

1090
01:23:17,758 --> 01:23:19,101
[STATIC CRACKLES OVER PA]

1091
01:23:23,697 --> 01:23:24,801
MOLLY:
Here we go.

1092
01:23:24,998 --> 01:23:27,535
WOMAN 1 [OVER PA]: The cabin lights
have been dimmed for takeoff.

1093
01:23:27,701 --> 01:23:30,375
[MAN 3 SPEAKING IN FRENCH OVER PA]

1094
01:23:50,590 --> 01:23:52,570
[KANSAS' "DUST IN THE WIND"
PLAYING ON HEADPHONES]

1095
01:23:52,726 --> 01:23:55,332
With curiosity

1096
01:23:56,730 --> 01:24:00,200
Dust in the wind

1097
01:24:05,372 --> 01:24:06,680
[MOLLY GASPS]

1098
01:24:12,412 --> 01:24:13,652
Sorry about that.

1099
01:24:15,982 --> 01:24:18,258
WOMAN 2:
Oh, excuse me.

1100
01:24:18,418 --> 01:24:23,094
Those passengers who got off the plane
earlier, what was that all about?

1101
01:24:23,256 --> 01:24:25,930
FLIGHT ATTENDANT: A kid had
a panic attack and wanted off the plane.

1102
01:24:26,259 --> 01:24:28,205
Said he had some kind of vision.

1103
01:24:29,062 --> 01:24:30,405
No.

1104
01:24:32,499 --> 01:24:33,603
Oh, my God!

1105
01:24:35,902 --> 01:24:37,848
[PASSENGERS SCREAMING]

1106
01:24:38,538 --> 01:24:39,573
Sam.

1107
01:24:59,826 --> 01:25:01,305
[SCREAMING]

1108
01:25:05,265 --> 01:25:08,041
[MOLLY SCREAMING]

1109
01:25:08,201 --> 01:25:09,339
SAM:
I get you!

1110
01:25:11,538 --> 01:25:14,485
-Sam!
-Molly, hold on!

1111
01:25:16,076 --> 01:25:17,111
No!

1112
01:25:17,277 --> 01:25:18,585
[SCREAMS]

1113
01:25:19,146 --> 01:25:20,819
No!

1114
01:25:23,116 --> 01:25:25,460
[SAM SCREAMING IN SLOW MOTION]

1115
01:25:34,828 --> 01:25:36,865
[KANSAS' "DUST IN THE WIND"
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

1116
01:25:37,030 --> 01:25:39,874
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1117
01:25:45,172 --> 01:25:46,708
Nice of you to come, Nathan.

1118
01:25:46,873 --> 01:25:49,149
I know Ray
wasn't the easiest guy to work with.

1119
01:25:50,210 --> 01:25:51,621
You know.

1120
01:25:51,778 --> 01:25:53,883
I still can't believe he's gone, though.

1121
01:25:54,047 --> 01:25:56,527
Yeah. Yeah, no kidding.

1122
01:25:56,683 --> 01:25:57,957
I guess it was for the best.

1123
01:25:59,419 --> 01:26:00,454
What do you mean?

1124
01:26:00,620 --> 01:26:03,794
Company did an autopsy
for insurance purposes.

1125
01:26:03,957 --> 01:26:07,029
Turns out Roy had an enlarged
blood vessel in his brain so big...

1126
01:26:07,194 --> 01:26:10,471
...it was about to burst.
They said he'd be dead any day now.

1127
01:26:10,630 --> 01:26:12,940
[OVER SPEAKERS]
Nothing lasts forever but the ....

1128
01:26:13,099 --> 01:26:14,737
Any day?

1129
01:26:15,702 --> 01:26:16,737
Life's a bitch.

1130
01:26:16,903 --> 01:26:18,712
Dust in the wind

1131
01:26:30,917 --> 01:26:32,328
[SCREAMS]

1132
01:26:34,487 --> 01:26:35,625
[TIRES SCREECH]

1133
01:26:39,659 --> 01:26:40,797
[GROANS]

1134
01:26:40,994 --> 01:26:42,064
[GROANS]

1135
01:27:11,224 --> 01:27:12,294
[MUFFLED SCREAM]

1136
01:27:29,376 --> 01:27:30,616
[SCREAMS]

1137
01:27:46,126 --> 01:27:47,764
[YELLS]

1138
01:27:59,139 --> 01:28:02,416
BLUDWORTH:
You all just be careful now.